other_tests.findings: Finnish patients harbored compound heterozygous loss-of-function variants in TBC1D32; Pakistani proband carried a known pathogenic homozygous TBC1D32 splice-site variant.

In Patient I.3, the sella turcica and hypophysis were not identifiable; an ectopic neurohypophysis was present near the tuber cinereum. In Patient I.5, MRI showed absent sella turcica and anterior pituitary gland; potential neurohypophyseal tissue was detected close to the tuber cinereum.

other_tests.procedure_name: Test for Growth Hormone concentration during hypoglycemia
other_tests.findings: Patient II.8 had a GH concentration of 0.6 ug/L in response to hypoglycemia.
Proper retinal responses; however, severe cerebral visual impairment with reduced visual acuity observed.
Investigated protein-protein interaction partners of TBC1D32.
